{"cursor":"4472","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Juan Rafael Bustillo' (born January 31, 1935) is a former general and chief of\nthe Air Force of El Salvador who is accused of planning the murder of\nsix Jesuit priests, a housekeeper and her daughter at the Universidad\nCentroamericana \"JosÃ© SimeÃ³n CaÃ±as\" (UCA) in El Salvador on November 16\n1989. [http://www.usip.org/library/-\ntc/doc/reports/el_salvador/tc_es_03151993_casesB1.html] United States Institute\nof Peace\n\nBustillo was born in San Miguel in 1935 to John and Elena Toledo Bustillo. He\nentered the Salvadoran Military Academy on February 1 1954, and was promoted to\nlieutenant in 1962, Captain in 1966, major in 1972, lieutenant colonel in 1976,\ncolonel in 1980 and general in 1984. [http://www.fas.gob.sv/jefa/excomandantes/bustillo.html] Biography\nof Bustillo by Air force Captain Douglas A. Cornejo\n\nBustillo is wanted in France for torturing, raping and murdering 27-year-old\nMadeleine Lagadec in El Salvador in 1989. Her raped, bullet-riddled body was\nfound with its left hand severed.\n\nAs the head of the Salvadoran Air Force, Bustillo oversaw the\nContras' operation of importing weapons into Nicaragua that were paid for by\ncrack cocaine smuggled into the United States. He is also accused of ordering\nAir Force officials to torture and murder members of the teachers union in El\nSalvador, including Maria Cristina Gomez.\n\nOn November 13, 2008, The Center for Justice and Accountability (CJA) filed a\ncriminal case in Madrid in Spain against former Salvadoran military officials,\nincluding Bustillo, for their role in the Jesuits Massacre of 1989. The CJA and\ntheir colleagues with the Spanish Association for Human Rights (APDHE) jointly\nfiled the case as prosecutors in the Spanish National Court, using Spainâs\nuniversal jurisdiction law. On January 13 2009, the 14 officers and soldiers\nnamed in the case were formally charged with crimes against humanity and state\nterrorism.\n\nBustillo resides in El Salvador.\n","linknr":131,"url":"Juan_Rafael_Bustillo","recorded":1375084412,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Juan_Rafael_Bustillo&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Juan_Rafael_Bustillo&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/General","/wiki/Air_Force_of_El_Salvador","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Society_of_Jesus","/wiki/Priesthood_(Catholic_Church)","/wiki/Universidad_Centroamericana_%22Jos%C3%A9_Sime%C3%B3n_Ca%C3%B1as%22","/wiki/El_Salvador","#cite_note-bustillo-2","#cite_note-cja-3","#cite_note-4","/wiki/San_Miguel,_El_Salvador","/wiki/Lieutenant","/wiki/Captain_(land_and_air)","/wiki/Major","/wiki/Lieutenant_colonel","/wiki/Colonel","#cite_note-Escobar-5","/wiki/France","#cite_note-cja2-6","#cite_note-7","/wiki/Contras","/wiki/Nicaragua","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Maria_Cristina_Gomez","#cite_note-bustillo-2","/wiki/Madrid","/wiki/Spain","#cite_note-cja2-6","/w/index.php?title=Juan_Rafael_Bustillo&action=edit&section=1","#cite_ref-1","http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=W9du-K7-6tsC&pg=PA75&lpg=PA75&dq=Juan+Rafael+Bustillo&source=bl&ots=H8EuPoGF8m&sig=biP-Ryt-ar9HwPQSQVJo5z3ffqQ&hl=en&ei=TpsJSrTsGpnKjAeTrO2xCw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4","/wiki/International_St